4006 /* PyFunctionFastCall */
4007 #if CYTHON_FAST_PYCALL
4008 static PyObject* __Pyx_PyFunction_FastCallNoKw(PyCodeObject *co, PyObject **args, Py_ssize_t na,
4009  PyObject *globals) {
4010  PyFrameObject *f;
4011  PyThreadState *tstate = __Pyx_PyThreadState_Current;
4012  PyObject **fastlocals;
4013  Py_ssize_t i;
4014  PyObject *result;
4015  assert(globals != NULL);
4016  /* XXX Perhaps we should create a specialized
4017  PyFrame_New() that doesn't take locals, but does
4018  take builtins without sanity checking them.
4019  */
4020  assert(tstate != NULL);
4021  f = PyFrame_New(tstate, co, globals, NULL);
4022  if (f == NULL) {
4023  return NULL;
4024  }
4025  fastlocals = __Pyx_PyFrame_GetLocalsplus(f);
4026  for (i = 0; i < na; i++) {
4027  Py_INCREF(*args);
4028  fastlocals[i] = *args++;
4029  }
4030  result = PyEval_EvalFrameEx(f,0);
4031  ++tstate->recursion_depth;
4032  Py_DECREF(f);
4033  --tstate->recursion_depth;
4034  return result;
4035 }
4036 #if 1 || PY_VERSION_HEX < 0x030600B1
4037 static PyObject *__Pyx_PyFunction_FastCallDict(PyObject *func, PyObject **args, Py_ssize_t nargs, PyObject *kwargs) {
4038  PyCodeObject *co = (PyCodeObject *)PyFunction_GET_CODE(func);
4039  PyObject *globals = PyFunction_GET_GLOBALS(func);
4040  PyObject *argdefs = PyFunction_GET_DEFAULTS(func);
4041  PyObject *closure;
4042 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
4043  PyObject *kwdefs;
4044 #endif
4045  PyObject *kwtuple, **k;
4046  PyObject **d;
4047  Py_ssize_t nd;
4048  Py_ssize_t nk;
4049  PyObject *result;
4050  assert(kwargs == NULL || PyDict_Check(kwargs));
4051  nk = kwargs ? PyDict_Size(kwargs) : 0;
4052  if (Py_EnterRecursiveCall((char*)" while calling a Python object")) {
4053  return NULL;
4054  }
4055  if (
4056 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
4057  co->co_kwonlyargcount == 0 &&
4058 #endif
4059  likely(kwargs == NULL || nk == 0) &&
4060  co->co_flags == (CO_OPTIMIZED | CO_NEWLOCALS | CO_NOFREE)) {
4061  if (argdefs == NULL && co->co_argcount == nargs) {
4062  result = __Pyx_PyFunction_FastCallNoKw(co, args, nargs, globals);
4063  goto done;
4064  }
4065  else if (nargs == 0 && argdefs != NULL
4066  && co->co_argcount == Py_SIZE(argdefs)) {
4067  /* function called with no arguments, but all parameters have
4068  a default value: use default values as arguments .*/
4069  args = &PyTuple_GET_ITEM(argdefs, 0);
4070  result =__Pyx_PyFunction_FastCallNoKw(co, args, Py_SIZE(argdefs), globals);
4071  goto done;
4072  }
4073  }
4074  if (kwargs != NULL) {
4075  Py_ssize_t pos, i;
4076  kwtuple = PyTuple_New(2 * nk);
4077  if (kwtuple == NULL) {
4078  result = NULL;
4079  goto done;
4080  }
4081  k = &PyTuple_GET_ITEM(kwtuple, 0);
4082  pos = i = 0;
4083  while (PyDict_Next(kwargs, &pos, &k[i], &k[i+1])) {
4084  Py_INCREF(k[i]);
4085  Py_INCREF(k[i+1]);
4086  i += 2;
4087  }
4088  nk = i / 2;
4089  }
4090  else {
4091  kwtuple = NULL;
4092  k = NULL;
4093  }
4094  closure = PyFunction_GET_CLOSURE(func);
4095 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
4096  kwdefs = PyFunction_GET_KW_DEFAULTS(func);
4097 #endif
4098  if (argdefs != NULL) {
4099  d = &PyTuple_GET_ITEM(argdefs, 0);
4100  nd = Py_SIZE(argdefs);
4101  }
4102  else {
4103  d = NULL;
4104  nd = 0;
4105  }
4106 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
4107  result = PyEval_EvalCodeEx((PyObject*)co, globals, (PyObject *)NULL,
4108  args, (int)nargs,
4109  k, (int)nk,
4110  d, (int)nd, kwdefs, closure);
4111 #else
4112  result = PyEval_EvalCodeEx(co, globals, (PyObject *)NULL,
4113  args, (int)nargs,
4114  k, (int)nk,
4115  d, (int)nd, closure);
4116 #endif
4117  Py_XDECREF(kwtuple);
4118 done:
4119  Py_LeaveRecursiveCall();
4120  return result;
4121 }
4122 #endif
4123 #endif

4125 /* PyCFunctionFastCall */
4126 #if CYTHON_FAST_PYCCALL
4127 static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject * __Pyx_PyCFunction_FastCall(PyObject *func_obj, PyObject **args, Py_ssize_t nargs) {
4128  PyCFunctionObject *func = (PyCFunctionObject*)func_obj;
4129  PyCFunction meth = PyCFunction_GET_FUNCTION(func);
4130  PyObject *self = PyCFunction_GET_SELF(func);
4131  int flags = PyCFunction_GET_FLAGS(func);
4132  assert(PyCFunction_Check(func));
4133  assert(METH_FASTCALL == (flags & ~(METH_CLASS | METH_STATIC | METH_COEXIST | METH_KEYWORDS | METH_STACKLESS)));
4134  assert(nargs >= 0);
4135  assert(nargs == 0 || args != NULL);
4136  /* _PyCFunction_FastCallDict() must not be called with an exception set,
4137  because it may clear it (directly or indirectly) and so the
4138  caller loses its exception */
4139  assert(!PyErr_Occurred());
4140  if ((PY_VERSION_HEX < 0x030700A0) || unlikely(flags & METH_KEYWORDS)) {
4141  return (*((__Pyx_PyCFunctionFastWithKeywords)(void*)meth)) (self, args, nargs, NULL);
4142  } else {
4143  return (*((__Pyx_PyCFunctionFast)(void*)meth)) (self, args, nargs);
4144  }
4145 }

4148 /* PyObjectCall */
4149 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_CPYTHON
4150 static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject* __Pyx_PyObject_Call(PyObject *func, PyObject *arg, PyObject *kw) {
4151  PyObject *result;
4152  ternaryfunc call = Py_TYPE(func)->tp_call;
4153  if (unlikely(!call))
4154  return PyObject_Call(func, arg, kw);
4155  if (unlikely(Py_EnterRecursiveCall((char*)" while calling a Python object")))
4156  return NULL;
4157  result = (*call)(func, arg, kw);
4158  Py_LeaveRecursiveCall();
4159  if (unlikely(!result) && unlikely(!PyErr_Occurred())) {
4160  PyErr_SetString(
4161  PyExc_SystemError,
4162  "NULL result without error in PyObject_Call");
4163  }
4164  return result;
4165 }

4170  PyObject *r;
4171  if (!j) return NULL;
4172  r = PyObject_GetItem(o, j);
4173  Py_DECREF(j);

4176 static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject *__Pyx_GetItemInt_List_Fast(PyObject *o, Py_ssize_t i,
4177  CYTHON_NCP_UNUSED int wraparound,
4178  CYTHON_NCP_UNUSED int boundscheck) {
4179 #if CYTHON_ASSUME_SAFE_MACROS && !CYTHON_AVOID_BORROWED_REFS
4180  Py_ssize_t wrapped_i = i;
4181  if (wraparound & unlikely(i < 0)) {
4182  wrapped_i += PyList_GET_SIZE(o);
4183  }
4184  if ((!boundscheck) || likely(__Pyx_is_valid_index(wrapped_i, PyList_GET_SIZE(o)))) {
4185  PyObject *r = PyList_GET_ITEM(o, wrapped_i);
4186  Py_INCREF(r);
4187  return r;
4188  }
4189  return __Pyx_GetItemInt_Generic(o, PyInt_FromSsize_t(i));
4190 #else
4191  return PySequence_GetItem(o, i);
4192 #endif
4193 }
4194 static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject *__Pyx_GetItemInt_Tuple_Fast(PyObject *o, Py_ssize_t i,
4195  CYTHON_NCP_UNUSED int wraparound,
4196  CYTHON_NCP_UNUSED int boundscheck) {
4197 #if CYTHON_ASSUME_SAFE_MACROS && !CYTHON_AVOID_BORROWED_REFS
4198  Py_ssize_t wrapped_i = i;
4199  if (wraparound & unlikely(i < 0)) {
4200  wrapped_i += PyTuple_GET_SIZE(o);
4201  }
4202  if ((!boundscheck) || likely(__Pyx_is_valid_index(wrapped_i, PyTuple_GET_SIZE(o)))) {
4203  PyObject *r = PyTuple_GET_ITEM(o, wrapped_i);
4204  Py_INCREF(r);
4205  return r;
4206  }
4207  return __Pyx_GetItemInt_Generic(o, PyInt_FromSsize_t(i));
4208 #else
4209  return PySequence_GetItem(o, i);
4210 #endif

4212 static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject *__Pyx_GetItemInt_Fast(PyObject *o, Py_ssize_t i, int is_list,
4213  CYTHON_NCP_UNUSED int wraparound,
4214  CYTHON_NCP_UNUSED int boundscheck) {
4215 #if CYTHON_ASSUME_SAFE_MACROS && !CYTHON_AVOID_BORROWED_REFS && CYTHON_USE_TYPE_SLOTS
4216  if (is_list || PyList_CheckExact(o)) {
4217  Py_ssize_t n = ((!wraparound) | likely(i >= 0)) ? i : i + PyList_GET_SIZE(o);
4218  if ((!boundscheck) || (likely(__Pyx_is_valid_index(n, PyList_GET_SIZE(o))))) {
4219  PyObject *r = PyList_GET_ITEM(o, n);
4220  Py_INCREF(r);
4221  return r;
4222  }
4223  }
4224  else if (PyTuple_CheckExact(o)) {
4225  Py_ssize_t n = ((!wraparound) | likely(i >= 0)) ? i : i + PyTuple_GET_SIZE(o);
4226  if ((!boundscheck) || likely(__Pyx_is_valid_index(n, PyTuple_GET_SIZE(o)))) {
4227  PyObject *r = PyTuple_GET_ITEM(o, n);
4228  Py_INCREF(r);
4229  return r;
4230  }
4231  } else {
4232  PySequenceMethods *m = Py_TYPE(o)->tp_as_sequence;
4233  if (likely(m && m->sq_item)) {
4234  if (wraparound && unlikely(i < 0) && likely(m->sq_length)) {
4235  Py_ssize_t l = m->sq_length(o);
4236  if (likely(l >= 0)) {
4237  i += l;
4238  } else {
4239  if (!PyErr_ExceptionMatches(PyExc_OverflowError))
4240  return NULL;
4241  PyErr_Clear();
4242  }
4243  }
4244  return m->sq_item(o, i);
4245  }
4246  }
4247 #else
4248  if (is_list || PySequence_Check(o)) {
4249  return PySequence_GetItem(o, i);
4250  }
4251 #endif
4252  return __Pyx_GetItemInt_Generic(o, PyInt_FromSsize_t(i));
4253 }

4310 /* IterFinish */
4311 static CYTHON_INLINE int __Pyx_IterFinish(void) {
4312 #if CYTHON_FAST_THREAD_STATE
4313  PyThreadState *tstate = __Pyx_PyThreadState_Current;
4314  PyObject* exc_type = tstate->curexc_type;
4315  if (unlikely(exc_type)) {
4316  if (likely(__Pyx_PyErr_GivenExceptionMatches(exc_type, PyExc_StopIteration))) {
4317  PyObject *exc_value, *exc_tb;
4318  exc_value = tstate->curexc_value;
4319  exc_tb = tstate->curexc_traceback;
4320  tstate->curexc_type = 0;
4321  tstate->curexc_value = 0;
4322  tstate->curexc_traceback = 0;
4323  Py_DECREF(exc_type);
4324  Py_XDECREF(exc_value);
4325  Py_XDECREF(exc_tb);
4326  return 0;
4327  } else {
4328  return -1;
4329  }
4330  }
4331  return 0;
4332 #else
4333  if (unlikely(PyErr_Occurred())) {
4334  if (likely(PyErr_ExceptionMatches(PyExc_StopIteration))) {
4335  PyErr_Clear();
4336  return 0;
4337  } else {
4338  return -1;
4339  }
4340  }
4341  return 0;
4342 #endif
4343 }

4345 /* UnpackItemEndCheck */
4346 static int __Pyx_IternextUnpackEndCheck(PyObject *retval, Py_ssize_t expected) {
4347  if (unlikely(retval)) {
4348  Py_DECREF(retval);
4349  __Pyx_RaiseTooManyValuesError(expected);
4350  return -1;
4351  }
4352  return __Pyx_IterFinish();
4353 }

4355 /* RaiseException */
4356 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
4357 static void __Pyx_Raise(PyObject *type, PyObject *value, PyObject *tb,
4358  CYTHON_UNUSED PyObject *cause) {
4359  __Pyx_PyThreadState_declare
4360  Py_XINCREF(type);
4361  if (!value || value == Py_None)
4362  value = NULL;
4363  else
4364  Py_INCREF(value);
4365  if (!tb || tb == Py_None)
4366  tb = NULL;
4367  else {
4368  Py_INCREF(tb);
4369  if (!PyTraceBack_Check(tb)) {
4370  PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
4371  "raise: arg 3 must be a traceback or None");
4372  goto raise_error;
4373  }
4374  }
4375  if (PyType_Check(type)) {
4376 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_PYPY
4377  if (!value) {
4378  Py_INCREF(Py_None);
4379  value = Py_None;
4380  }
4381 #endif
4382  PyErr_NormalizeException(&type, &value, &tb);
4383  } else {
4384  if (value) {
4385  PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
4386  "instance exception may not have a separate value");
4387  goto raise_error;
4388  }
4389  value = type;
4390  type = (PyObject*) Py_TYPE(type);
4391  Py_INCREF(type);
4392  if (!PyType_IsSubtype((PyTypeObject *)type, (PyTypeObject *)PyExc_BaseException)) {
4393  PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
4394  "raise: exception class must be a subclass of BaseException");
4395  goto raise_error;
4396  }
4397  }
4398  __Pyx_PyThreadState_assign
4399  __Pyx_ErrRestore(type, value, tb);
4400  return;
4401 raise_error:
4402  Py_XDECREF(value);
4403  Py_XDECREF(type);
4404  Py_XDECREF(tb);
4405  return;
4406 }
4407 #else
4408 static void __Pyx_Raise(PyObject *type, PyObject *value, PyObject *tb, PyObject *cause) {
4409  PyObject* owned_instance = NULL;
4410  if (tb == Py_None) {
4411  tb = 0;
4412  } else if (tb && !PyTraceBack_Check(tb)) {
4413  PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
4414  "raise: arg 3 must be a traceback or None");
4415  goto bad;
4416  }
4417  if (value == Py_None)
4418  value = 0;
4419  if (PyExceptionInstance_Check(type)) {
4420  if (value) {
4421  PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
4422  "instance exception may not have a separate value");
4423  goto bad;
4424  }
4425  value = type;
4426  type = (PyObject*) Py_TYPE(value);
4427  } else if (PyExceptionClass_Check(type)) {
4428  PyObject *instance_class = NULL;
4429  if (value && PyExceptionInstance_Check(value)) {
4430  instance_class = (PyObject*) Py_TYPE(value);
4431  if (instance_class != type) {
4432  int is_subclass = PyObject_IsSubclass(instance_class, type);
4433  if (!is_subclass) {
4434  instance_class = NULL;
4435  } else if (unlikely(is_subclass == -1)) {
4436  goto bad;
4437  } else {
4438  type = instance_class;
4439  }
4440  }
4441  }
4442  if (!instance_class) {
4443  PyObject *args;
4444  if (!value)
4445  args = PyTuple_New(0);
4446  else if (PyTuple_Check(value)) {
4447  Py_INCREF(value);
4448  args = value;
4449  } else
4450  args = PyTuple_Pack(1, value);
4451  if (!args)
4452  goto bad;
4453  owned_instance = PyObject_Call(type, args, NULL);
4454  Py_DECREF(args);
4455  if (!owned_instance)
4456  goto bad;
4457  value = owned_instance;
4458  if (!PyExceptionInstance_Check(value)) {
4459  PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
4460  "calling %R should have returned an instance of "
4461  "BaseException, not %R",
4462  type, Py_TYPE(value));
4463  goto bad;
4464  }
4465  }
4466  } else {
4467  PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
4468  "raise: exception class must be a subclass of BaseException");
4469  goto bad;
4470  }
4471  if (cause) {
4472  PyObject *fixed_cause;
4473  if (cause == Py_None) {
4474  fixed_cause = NULL;
4475  } else if (PyExceptionClass_Check(cause)) {
4476  fixed_cause = PyObject_CallObject(cause, NULL);
4477  if (fixed_cause == NULL)
4478  goto bad;
4479  } else if (PyExceptionInstance_Check(cause)) {
4480  fixed_cause = cause;
4481  Py_INCREF(fixed_cause);
4482  } else {
4483  PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
4484  "exception causes must derive from "
4485  "BaseException");
4486  goto bad;
4487  }
4488  PyException_SetCause(value, fixed_cause);
4489  }
4490  PyErr_SetObject(type, value);
4491  if (tb) {
4492 #if CYTHON_FAST_THREAD_STATE
4493  PyThreadState *tstate = __Pyx_PyThreadState_Current;
4494  PyObject* tmp_tb = tstate->curexc_traceback;
4495  if (tb != tmp_tb) {
4496  Py_INCREF(tb);
4497  tstate->curexc_traceback = tb;
4498  Py_XDECREF(tmp_tb);
4499  }
4500 #else
4501  PyObject *tmp_type, *tmp_value, *tmp_tb;
4502  PyErr_Fetch(&tmp_type, &tmp_value, &tmp_tb);
4503  Py_INCREF(tb);
4504  PyErr_Restore(tmp_type, tmp_value, tb);
4505  Py_XDECREF(tmp_tb);
4506 #endif
4507  }
4508 bad:
4509  Py_XDECREF(owned_instance);
4510  return;
4511 }
4512 #endif
4513 
4514 /* TypeImport */
4515 #ifndef __PYX_HAVE_RT_ImportType_0_29_36
4516 #define __PYX_HAVE_RT_ImportType_0_29_36
4517 static PyTypeObject *__Pyx_ImportType_0_29_36(PyObject *module, const char *module_name, const char *class_name,
4518  size_t size, size_t alignment, enum __Pyx_ImportType_CheckSize_0_29_36 check_size)
4519 {
4520  PyObject *result = 0;
4521  char warning[200];
4522  Py_ssize_t basicsize;
4523  Py_ssize_t itemsize;
4524 #ifdef Py_LIMITED_API
4525  PyObject *py_basicsize;
4526  PyObject *py_itemsize;
4527 #endif
4528  result = PyObject_GetAttrString(module, class_name);
4529  if (!result)
4530  goto bad;
4531  if (!PyType_Check(result)) {
4532  PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
4533  "%.200s.%.200s is not a type object",
4534  module_name, class_name);
4535  goto bad;
4536  }
4537 #ifndef Py_LIMITED_API
4538  basicsize = ((PyTypeObject *)result)->tp_basicsize;
4539  itemsize = ((PyTypeObject *)result)->tp_itemsize;
4540 #else
4541  py_basicsize = PyObject_GetAttrString(result, "__basicsize__");
4542  if (!py_basicsize)
4543  goto bad;
4544  basicsize = PyLong_AsSsize_t(py_basicsize);
4545  Py_DECREF(py_basicsize);
4546  py_basicsize = 0;
4547  if (basicsize == (Py_ssize_t)-1 && PyErr_Occurred())
4548  goto bad;
4549  py_itemsize = PyObject_GetAttrString(result, "__itemsize__");
4550  if (!py_itemsize)
4551  goto bad;
4552  itemsize = PyLong_AsSsize_t(py_itemsize);
4553  Py_DECREF(py_itemsize);
4554  py_itemsize = 0;
4555  if (itemsize == (Py_ssize_t)-1 && PyErr_Occurred())
4556  goto bad;
4557 #endif
4558  if (itemsize) {
4559  if (size % alignment) {
4560  alignment = size % alignment;
4561  }
4562  if (itemsize < (Py_ssize_t)alignment)
4563  itemsize = (Py_ssize_t)alignment;
4564  }
4565  if ((size_t)(basicsize + itemsize) < size) {
4566  PyErr_Format(PyExc_ValueError,
4567  "%.200s.%.200s size changed, may indicate binary incompatibility. "
4568  "Expected %zd from C header, got %zd from PyObject",
4569  module_name, class_name, size, basicsize);
4570  goto bad;
4571  }
4572  if (check_size == __Pyx_ImportType_CheckSize_Error_0_29_36 && (size_t)basicsize != size) {
4573  PyErr_Format(PyExc_ValueError,
4574  "%.200s.%.200s size changed, may indicate binary incompatibility. "
4575  "Expected %zd from C header, got %zd from PyObject",
4576  module_name, class_name, size, basicsize);
4577  goto bad;
4578  }
4579  else if (check_size == __Pyx_ImportType_CheckSize_Warn_0_29_36 && (size_t)basicsize > size) {
4580  PyOS_snprintf(warning, sizeof(warning),
4581  "%s.%s size changed, may indicate binary incompatibility. "
4582  "Expected %zd from C header, got %zd from PyObject",
4583  module_name, class_name, size, basicsize);
4584  if (PyErr_WarnEx(NULL, warning, 0) < 0) goto bad;
4585  }
4586  return (PyTypeObject *)result;
4587 bad:
4588  Py_XDECREF(result);
4589  return NULL;
4590 }
4591 #endif

4605  PyErr_SetString(PyExc_RuntimeError, "invalid vtable found for imported type");
4606  Py_DECREF(ob);

4613 /* Import */
4614 static PyObject *__Pyx_Import(PyObject *name, PyObject *from_list, int level) {
4615  PyObject *empty_list = 0;
4616  PyObject *module = 0;
4617  PyObject *global_dict = 0;
4618  PyObject *empty_dict = 0;
4619  PyObject *list;
4620  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
4621  PyObject *py_import;
4622  py_import = __Pyx_PyObject_GetAttrStr(__pyx_b, __pyx_n_s_import);
4623  if (!py_import)
4624  goto bad;
4625  #endif
4626  if (from_list)
4627  list = from_list;
4628  else {
4629  empty_list = PyList_New(0);
4630  if (!empty_list)
4631  goto bad;
4632  list = empty_list;
4633  }
4634  global_dict = PyModule_GetDict(__pyx_m);
4635  if (!global_dict)
4636  goto bad;
4637  empty_dict = PyDict_New();
4638  if (!empty_dict)
4639  goto bad;
4640  {
4641  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
4642  if (level == -1) {
4643  if ((1) && (strchr(__Pyx_MODULE_NAME, '.'))) {
4644  module = PyImport_ImportModuleLevelObject(
4645  name, global_dict, empty_dict, list, 1);
4646  if (!module) {
4647  if (!PyErr_ExceptionMatches(PyExc_ImportError))
4648  goto bad;
4649  PyErr_Clear();
4650  }
4651  }
4652  level = 0;
4653  }
4654  #endif
4655  if (!module) {
4656  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
4657  PyObject *py_level = PyInt_FromLong(level);
4658  if (!py_level)
4659  goto bad;
4660  module = PyObject_CallFunctionObjArgs(py_import,
4661  name, global_dict, empty_dict, list, py_level, (PyObject *)NULL);
4662  Py_DECREF(py_level);
4663  #else
4664  module = PyImport_ImportModuleLevelObject(
4665  name, global_dict, empty_dict, list, level);
4666  #endif
4667  }
4668  }
4669 bad:
4670  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
4671  Py_XDECREF(py_import);
4672  #endif
4673  Py_XDECREF(empty_list);
4674  Py_XDECREF(empty_dict);
4675  return module;
4676 }

4692 /* FetchCommonType */
4693 static PyTypeObject* __Pyx_FetchCommonType(PyTypeObject* type) {
4694  PyObject* fake_module;
4695  PyTypeObject* cached_type = NULL;
4696  fake_module = PyImport_AddModule((char*) "_cython_" CYTHON_ABI);
4697  if (!fake_module) return NULL;
4698  Py_INCREF(fake_module);
4699  cached_type = (PyTypeObject*) PyObject_GetAttrString(fake_module, type->tp_name);
4700  if (cached_type) {
4701  if (!PyType_Check((PyObject*)cached_type)) {
4702  PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
4703  "Shared Cython type %.200s is not a type object",
4704  type->tp_name);
4705  goto bad;
4706  }
4707  if (cached_type->tp_basicsize != type->tp_basicsize) {
4708  PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
4709  "Shared Cython type %.200s has the wrong size, try recompiling",
4710  type->tp_name);
4711  goto bad;
4712  }
4713  } else {
4714  if (!PyErr_ExceptionMatches(PyExc_AttributeError)) goto bad;
4715  PyErr_Clear();
4716  if (PyType_Ready(type) < 0) goto bad;
4717  if (PyObject_SetAttrString(fake_module, type->tp_name, (PyObject*) type) < 0)
4718  goto bad;
4719  Py_INCREF(type);
4720  cached_type = type;
4721  }
4722 done:
4723  Py_DECREF(fake_module);
4724  return cached_type;
4725 bad:
4726  Py_XDECREF(cached_type);
4727  cached_type = NULL;
4728  goto done;
4729 }

4918  Py_INCREF(value);
4919  tmp = op->defaults_tuple;
4920  op->defaults_tuple = value;
4921  Py_XDECREF(tmp);
4922  return 0;
4923 }

4931  } else {

4933  }

5039 static PyObject *__Pyx_CyFunction_Init(__pyx_CyFunctionObject *op, PyMethodDef *ml, int flags, PyObject* qualname,
5040  PyObject *closure, PyObject *module, PyObject* globals, PyObject* code) {
5041  if (unlikely(op == NULL))
5042  return NULL;
5043  op->flags = flags;
5044  __Pyx_CyFunction_weakreflist(op) = NULL;
5045  op->func.m_ml = ml;
5046  op->func.m_self = (PyObject *) op;
5047  Py_XINCREF(closure);

5049  Py_XINCREF(module);

5052  op->func_name = NULL;

5056  op->func_classobj = NULL;

5058  Py_INCREF(op->func_globals);
5059  Py_XINCREF(code);
5060  op->func_code = code;
5061  op->defaults_pyobjects = 0;
5062  op->defaults_size = 0;
5063  op->defaults = NULL;
5064  op->defaults_tuple = NULL;
5065  op->defaults_kwdict = NULL;
5066  op->defaults_getter = NULL;
5067  op->func_annotations = NULL;

5128 static PyObject *__Pyx_CyFunction_descr_get(PyObject *func, PyObject *obj, PyObject *type)
5129 {
5130 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
5131  __pyx_CyFunctionObject *m = (__pyx_CyFunctionObject *) func;
5132  if (m->flags & __Pyx_CYFUNCTION_STATICMETHOD) {
5133  Py_INCREF(func);
5134  return func;
5135  }
5136  if (m->flags & __Pyx_CYFUNCTION_CLASSMETHOD) {
5137  if (type == NULL)
5138  type = (PyObject *)(Py_TYPE(obj));
5139  return __Pyx_PyMethod_New(func, type, (PyObject *)(Py_TYPE(type)));
5140  }
5141  if (obj == Py_None)
5142  obj = NULL;
5143 #endif
5144  return __Pyx_PyMethod_New(func, obj, type);
5145 }

5157 static PyObject * __Pyx_CyFunction_CallMethod(PyObject *func, PyObject *self, PyObject *arg, PyObject *kw) {
5158  PyCFunctionObject* f = (PyCFunctionObject*)func;
5159  PyCFunction meth = f->m_ml->ml_meth;
5160  Py_ssize_t size;
5161  switch (f->m_ml->ml_flags & (METH_VARARGS | METH_KEYWORDS | METH_NOARGS | METH_O)) {
5162  case METH_VARARGS:
5163  if (likely(kw == NULL || PyDict_Size(kw) == 0))
5164  return (*meth)(self, arg);
5165  break;
5166  case METH_VARARGS | METH_KEYWORDS:
5167  return (*(PyCFunctionWithKeywords)(void*)meth)(self, arg, kw);
5168  case METH_NOARGS:
5169  if (likely(kw == NULL || PyDict_Size(kw) == 0)) {
5170  size = PyTuple_GET_SIZE(arg);
5171  if (likely(size == 0))
5172  return (*meth)(self, NULL);
5173  PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
5174  "%.200s() takes no arguments (%" CYTHON_FORMAT_SSIZE_T "d given)",
5175  f->m_ml->ml_name, size);
5176  return NULL;
5177  }
5178  break;
5179  case METH_O:
5180  if (likely(kw == NULL || PyDict_Size(kw) == 0)) {
5181  size = PyTuple_GET_SIZE(arg);
5182  if (likely(size == 1)) {
5183  PyObject *result, *arg0;
5184  #if CYTHON_ASSUME_SAFE_MACROS && !CYTHON_AVOID_BORROWED_REFS
5185  arg0 = PyTuple_GET_ITEM(arg, 0);
5186  #else
5187  arg0 = PySequence_ITEM(arg, 0); if (unlikely(!arg0)) return NULL;
5188  #endif
5189  result = (*meth)(self, arg0);
5190  #if !(CYTHON_ASSUME_SAFE_MACROS && !CYTHON_AVOID_BORROWED_REFS)
5191  Py_DECREF(arg0);
5192  #endif
5193  return result;
5194  }
5195  PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
5196  "%.200s() takes exactly one argument (%" CYTHON_FORMAT_SSIZE_T "d given)",
5197  f->m_ml->ml_name, size);
5198  return NULL;
5199  }
5200  break;
5201  default:
5202  PyErr_SetString(PyExc_SystemError, "Bad call flags in "
5203  "__Pyx_CyFunction_Call. METH_OLDARGS is no "
5204  "longer supported!");
5205  return NULL;
5206  }
5207  PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError, "%.200s() takes no keyword arguments",
5208  f->m_ml->ml_name);
5209  return NULL;
5210 }
5211 static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject *__Pyx_CyFunction_Call(PyObject *func, PyObject *arg, PyObject *kw) {
5212  return __Pyx_CyFunction_CallMethod(func, ((PyCFunctionObject*)func)->m_self, arg, kw);
5213 }
5214 static PyObject *__Pyx_CyFunction_CallAsMethod(PyObject *func, PyObject *args, PyObject *kw) {
5215  PyObject *result;
5216  __pyx_CyFunctionObject *cyfunc = (__pyx_CyFunctionObject *) func;
5217  if ((cyfunc->flags & __Pyx_CYFUNCTION_CCLASS) && !(cyfunc->flags & __Pyx_CYFUNCTION_STATICMETHOD)) {
5218  Py_ssize_t argc;
5219  PyObject *new_args;
5220  PyObject *self;
5221  argc = PyTuple_GET_SIZE(args);
5222  new_args = PyTuple_GetSlice(args, 1, argc);
5223  if (unlikely(!new_args))
5224  return NULL;
5225  self = PyTuple_GetItem(args, 0);
5226  if (unlikely(!self)) {
5227  Py_DECREF(new_args);
5228 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION > 2
5229  PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
5230  "unbound method %.200S() needs an argument",
5231  cyfunc->func_qualname);
5232 #else
5233  PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
5234  "unbound method needs an argument");
5235 #endif
5236  return NULL;
5237  }
5238  result = __Pyx_CyFunction_CallMethod(func, self, new_args, kw);
5239  Py_DECREF(new_args);
5240  } else {
5241  result = __Pyx_CyFunction_Call(func, args, kw);
5242  }
5243  return result;
5244 }

5363 /* CLineInTraceback */
5364 #ifndef CYTHON_CLINE_IN_TRACEBACK
5365 static int __Pyx_CLineForTraceback(CYTHON_UNUSED PyThreadState *tstate, int c_line) {
5366  PyObject *use_cline;
5367  PyObject *ptype, *pvalue, *ptraceback;
5368 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_CPYTHON
5369  PyObject **cython_runtime_dict;
5370 #endif
5371  if (unlikely(!__pyx_cython_runtime)) {
5372  return c_line;
5373  }
5374  __Pyx_ErrFetchInState(tstate, &ptype, &pvalue, &ptraceback);
5375 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_CPYTHON
5376  cython_runtime_dict = _PyObject_GetDictPtr(__pyx_cython_runtime);
5377  if (likely(cython_runtime_dict)) {
5378  __PYX_PY_DICT_LOOKUP_IF_MODIFIED(
5379  use_cline, *cython_runtime_dict,
5380  __Pyx_PyDict_GetItemStr(*cython_runtime_dict, __pyx_n_s_cline_in_traceback))
5381  } else
5382 #endif
5383  {
5384  PyObject *use_cline_obj = __Pyx_PyObject_GetAttrStr(__pyx_cython_runtime, __pyx_n_s_cline_in_traceback);
5385  if (use_cline_obj) {
5386  use_cline = PyObject_Not(use_cline_obj) ? Py_False : Py_True;
5387  Py_DECREF(use_cline_obj);
5388  } else {
5389  PyErr_Clear();
5390  use_cline = NULL;
5391  }
5392  }
5393  if (!use_cline) {
5394  c_line = 0;
5395  (void) PyObject_SetAttr(__pyx_cython_runtime, __pyx_n_s_cline_in_traceback, Py_False);
5396  }
5397  else if (use_cline == Py_False || (use_cline != Py_True && PyObject_Not(use_cline) != 0)) {
5398  c_line = 0;
5399  }
5400  __Pyx_ErrRestoreInState(tstate, ptype, pvalue, ptraceback);
5401  return c_line;
5402 }
5403 #endif
5404 
5405 /* CodeObjectCache */
5406 static int __pyx_bisect_code_objects(__Pyx_CodeObjectCacheEntry* entries, int count, int code_line) {
5407  int start = 0, mid = 0, end = count - 1;
5408  if (end >= 0 && code_line > entries[end].code_line) {
5409  return count;
5410  }
5411  while (start < end) {
5412  mid = start + (end - start) / 2;
5413  if (code_line < entries[mid].code_line) {
5414  end = mid;
5415  } else if (code_line > entries[mid].code_line) {
5416  start = mid + 1;
5417  } else {
5418  return mid;
5419  }
5420  }
5421  if (code_line <= entries[mid].code_line) {
5422  return mid;
5423  } else {
5424  return mid + 1;
5425  }
5426 }
5427 static PyCodeObject *__pyx_find_code_object(int code_line) {
5428  PyCodeObject* code_object;
5429  int pos;
5430  if (unlikely(!code_line) || unlikely(!__pyx_code_cache.entries)) {
5431  return NULL;
5432  }
5433  pos = __pyx_bisect_code_objects(__pyx_code_cache.entries, __pyx_code_cache.count, code_line);
5434  if (unlikely(pos >= __pyx_code_cache.count) || unlikely(__pyx_code_cache.entries[pos].code_line != code_line)) {
5435  return NULL;
5436  }
5437  code_object = __pyx_code_cache.entries[pos].code_object;
5438  Py_INCREF(code_object);
5439  return code_object;
5440 }
5441 static void __pyx_insert_code_object(int code_line, PyCodeObject* code_object) {
5442  int pos, i;
5443  __Pyx_CodeObjectCacheEntry* entries = __pyx_code_cache.entries;
5444  if (unlikely(!code_line)) {
5445  return;
5446  }
5447  if (unlikely(!entries)) {
5448  entries = (__Pyx_CodeObjectCacheEntry*)PyMem_Malloc(64*sizeof(__Pyx_CodeObjectCacheEntry));
5449  if (likely(entries)) {
5450  __pyx_code_cache.entries = entries;
5451  __pyx_code_cache.max_count = 64;
5452  __pyx_code_cache.count = 1;
5453  entries[0].code_line = code_line;
5454  entries[0].code_object = code_object;
5455  Py_INCREF(code_object);
5456  }
5457  return;
5458  }
5459  pos = __pyx_bisect_code_objects(__pyx_code_cache.entries, __pyx_code_cache.count, code_line);
5460  if ((pos < __pyx_code_cache.count) && unlikely(__pyx_code_cache.entries[pos].code_line == code_line)) {
5461  PyCodeObject* tmp = entries[pos].code_object;
5462  entries[pos].code_object = code_object;
5463  Py_DECREF(tmp);
5464  return;
5465  }
5466  if (__pyx_code_cache.count == __pyx_code_cache.max_count) {
5467  int new_max = __pyx_code_cache.max_count + 64;
5468  entries = (__Pyx_CodeObjectCacheEntry*)PyMem_Realloc(
5469  __pyx_code_cache.entries, ((size_t)new_max) * sizeof(__Pyx_CodeObjectCacheEntry));
5470  if (unlikely(!entries)) {
5471  return;
5472  }
5473  __pyx_code_cache.entries = entries;
5474  __pyx_code_cache.max_count = new_max;
5475  }
5476  for (i=__pyx_code_cache.count; i>pos; i--) {
5477  entries[i] = entries[i-1];
5478  }
5479  entries[pos].code_line = code_line;
5480  entries[pos].code_object = code_object;
5481  __pyx_code_cache.count++;
5482  Py_INCREF(code_object);
5483 }

5485 /* AddTraceback */
5486 #include "compile.h"
5487 #include "frameobject.h"
5488 #include "traceback.h"
5489 #if PY_VERSION_HEX >= 0x030b00a6
5490  #ifndef Py_BUILD_CORE
5491  #define Py_BUILD_CORE 1
5492  #endif
5493  #include "internal/pycore_frame.h"
5494 #endif
5495 static PyCodeObject* __Pyx_CreateCodeObjectForTraceback(
5496  const char *funcname, int c_line,
5497  int py_line, const char *filename) {
5498  PyCodeObject *py_code = NULL;
5499  PyObject *py_funcname = NULL;
5500  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
5501  PyObject *py_srcfile = NULL;
5502  py_srcfile = PyString_FromString(filename);
5503  if (!py_srcfile) goto bad;
5504  #endif
5505  if (c_line) {
5506  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
5507  py_funcname = PyString_FromFormat( "%s (%s:%d)", funcname, __pyx_cfilenm, c_line);
5508  if (!py_funcname) goto bad;
5509  #else
5510  py_funcname = PyUnicode_FromFormat( "%s (%s:%d)", funcname, __pyx_cfilenm, c_line);
5511  if (!py_funcname) goto bad;
5512  funcname = PyUnicode_AsUTF8(py_funcname);
5513  if (!funcname) goto bad;
5514  #endif
5515  }
5516  else {
5517  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
5518  py_funcname = PyString_FromString(funcname);
5519  if (!py_funcname) goto bad;
5520  #endif
5521  }
5522  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
5523  py_code = __Pyx_PyCode_New(
5524  0,
5525  0,
5526  0,
5527  0,
5528  0,
5529  __pyx_empty_bytes, /*PyObject *code,*/
5530  __pyx_empty_tuple, /*PyObject *consts,*/
5531  __pyx_empty_tuple, /*PyObject *names,*/
5532  __pyx_empty_tuple, /*PyObject *varnames,*/
5533  __pyx_empty_tuple, /*PyObject *freevars,*/
5534  __pyx_empty_tuple, /*PyObject *cellvars,*/
5535  py_srcfile, /*PyObject *filename,*/
5536  py_funcname, /*PyObject *name,*/
5537  py_line,
5538  __pyx_empty_bytes /*PyObject *lnotab*/
5539  );
5540  Py_DECREF(py_srcfile);
5541  #else
5542  py_code = PyCode_NewEmpty(filename, funcname, py_line);
5543  #endif
5544  Py_XDECREF(py_funcname); // XDECREF since it's only set on Py3 if cline
5545  return py_code;
5546 bad:
5547  Py_XDECREF(py_funcname);
5548  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
5549  Py_XDECREF(py_srcfile);
5550  #endif
5551  return NULL;
5552 }
5553 static void __Pyx_AddTraceback(const char *funcname, int c_line,
5554  int py_line, const char *filename) {
5555  PyCodeObject *py_code = 0;
5556  PyFrameObject *py_frame = 0;
5557  PyThreadState *tstate = __Pyx_PyThreadState_Current;
5558  PyObject *ptype, *pvalue, *ptraceback;
5559  if (c_line) {
5560  c_line = __Pyx_CLineForTraceback(tstate, c_line);
5561  }
5562  py_code = __pyx_find_code_object(c_line ? -c_line : py_line);
5563  if (!py_code) {
5564  __Pyx_ErrFetchInState(tstate, &ptype, &pvalue, &ptraceback);
5565  py_code = __Pyx_CreateCodeObjectForTraceback(
5566  funcname, c_line, py_line, filename);
5567  if (!py_code) {
5568  /* If the code object creation fails, then we should clear the
5569  fetched exception references and propagate the new exception */
5570  Py_XDECREF(ptype);
5571  Py_XDECREF(pvalue);
5572  Py_XDECREF(ptraceback);
5573  goto bad;
5574  }
5575  __Pyx_ErrRestoreInState(tstate, ptype, pvalue, ptraceback);
5576  __pyx_insert_code_object(c_line ? -c_line : py_line, py_code);
5577  }
5578  py_frame = PyFrame_New(
5579  tstate, /*PyThreadState *tstate,*/
5580  py_code, /*PyCodeObject *code,*/
5581  __pyx_d, /*PyObject *globals,*/
5582  0 /*PyObject *locals*/
5583  );
5584  if (!py_frame) goto bad;
5585  __Pyx_PyFrame_SetLineNumber(py_frame, py_line);
5586  PyTraceBack_Here(py_frame);
5587 bad:
5588  Py_XDECREF(py_code);
5589  Py_XDECREF(py_frame);
5590 }

5592 /* CIntToPy */
5593 static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject* __Pyx_PyInt_From_long(long value) {
5594 #ifdef __Pyx_HAS_GCC_DIAGNOSTIC
5595 #pragma GCC diagnostic push
5596 #pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Wconversion"
5597 #endif
5598  const long neg_one = (long) -1, const_zero = (long) 0;
5599 #ifdef __Pyx_HAS_GCC_DIAGNOSTIC
5600 #pragma GCC diagnostic pop
5601 #endif
5602  const int is_unsigned = neg_one > const_zero;
5603  if (is_unsigned) {
5604  if (sizeof(long) < sizeof(long)) {
5605  return PyInt_FromLong((long) value);
5606  } else if (sizeof(long) <= sizeof(unsigned long)) {
5607  return PyLong_FromUnsignedLong((unsigned long) value);
5608 #ifdef HAVE_LONG_LONG
5609  } else if (sizeof(long) <= sizeof(unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)) {
5610  return PyLong_FromUnsignedLongLong((unsigned PY_LONG_LONG) value);
5611 #endif
5612  }
5613  } else {
5614  if (sizeof(long) <= sizeof(long)) {
5615  return PyInt_FromLong((long) value);
5616 #ifdef HAVE_LONG_LONG
5617  } else if (sizeof(long) <= sizeof(PY_LONG_LONG)) {
5618  return PyLong_FromLongLong((PY_LONG_LONG) value);
5619 #endif
5620  }
5621  }
5622  {
5623  int one = 1; int little = (int)*(unsigned char *)&one;
5624  unsigned char *bytes = (unsigned char *)&value;
5625  return _PyLong_FromByteArray(bytes, sizeof(long),
5626  little, !is_unsigned);
5627  }
5628 }

5630 /* CIntFromPyVerify */
5631 #define __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT(target_type, func_type, func_value)\
5632  __PYX__VERIFY_RETURN_INT(target_type, func_type, func_value, 0)
5633 #define __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT_EXC(target_type, func_type, func_value)\
5634  __PYX__VERIFY_RETURN_INT(target_type, func_type, func_value, 1)
5635 #define __PYX__VERIFY_RETURN_INT(target_type, func_type, func_value, exc)\
5636  {\
5637  func_type value = func_value;\
5638  if (sizeof(target_type) < sizeof(func_type)) {\
5639  if (unlikely(value != (func_type) (target_type) value)) {\
5640  func_type zero = 0;\
5641  if (exc && unlikely(value == (func_type)-1 && PyErr_Occurred()))\
5642  return (target_type) -1;\
5643  if (is_unsigned && unlikely(value < zero))\
5644  goto raise_neg_overflow;\
5645  else\
5646  goto raise_overflow;\
5647  }\
5648  }\
5649  return (target_type) value;\
5650  }

5652 /* CIntFromPy */
5653 static CYTHON_INLINE long __Pyx_PyInt_As_long(PyObject *x) {
5654 #ifdef __Pyx_HAS_GCC_DIAGNOSTIC
5655 #pragma GCC diagnostic push
5656 #pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Wconversion"
5657 #endif
5658  const long neg_one = (long) -1, const_zero = (long) 0;
5659 #ifdef __Pyx_HAS_GCC_DIAGNOSTIC
5660 #pragma GCC diagnostic pop
5661 #endif
5662  const int is_unsigned = neg_one > const_zero;
5663 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
5664  if (likely(PyInt_Check(x))) {
5665  if (sizeof(long) < sizeof(long)) {
5666  __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT(long, long, PyInt_AS_LONG(x))
5667  } else {
5668  long val = PyInt_AS_LONG(x);
5669  if (is_unsigned && unlikely(val < 0)) {
5670  goto raise_neg_overflow;
5671  }
5672  return (long) val;
5673  }
5674  } else
5675 #endif
5676  if (likely(PyLong_Check(x))) {
5677  if (is_unsigned) {
5678 #if CYTHON_USE_PYLONG_INTERNALS
5679  const digit* digits = ((PyLongObject*)x)->ob_digit;
5680  switch (Py_SIZE(x)) {
5681  case 0: return (long) 0;
5682  case 1: __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT(long, digit, digits[0])
5683  case 2:
5684  if (8 * sizeof(long) > 1 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
5685  if (8 * sizeof(unsigned long) > 2 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
5686  __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT(long, unsigned long, (((((unsigned long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[0])))
5687  } else if (8 * sizeof(long) >= 2 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
5688  return (long) (((((long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (long)digits[0]));
5689  }
5690  }
5691  break;
5692  case 3:
5693  if (8 * sizeof(long) > 2 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
5694  if (8 * sizeof(unsigned long) > 3 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
5695  __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT(long, unsigned long, (((((((unsigned long)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[0])))
5696  } else if (8 * sizeof(long) >= 3 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
5697  return (long) (((((((long)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (long)digits[0]));
5698  }
5699  }
5700  break;
5701  case 4:
5702  if (8 * sizeof(long) > 3 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
5703  if (8 * sizeof(unsigned long) > 4 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
5704  __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT(long, unsigned long, (((((((((unsigned long)digits[3]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[0])))
5705  } else if (8 * sizeof(long) >= 4 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
5706  return (long) (((((((((long)digits[3]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (long)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (long)digits[0]));
5707  }
5708  }
5709  break;
5710  }
5711 #endif
5712 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_CPYTHON && PY_VERSION_HEX < 0x030C00A7
5713  if (unlikely(Py_SIZE(x) < 0)) {
5714  goto raise_neg_overflow;
5715  }
5716 #else
5717  {
5718  int result = PyObject_RichCompareBool(x, Py_False, Py_LT);
5719  if (unlikely(result < 0))
5720  return (long) -1;
5721  if (unlikely(result == 1))
5722  goto raise_neg_overflow;
5723  }
5724 #endif
5725  if (sizeof(long) <= sizeof(unsigned long)) {
5726  __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT_EXC(long, unsigned long, PyLong_AsUnsignedLong(x))
5727 #ifdef HAVE_LONG_LONG
5728  } else if (sizeof(long) <= sizeof(unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)) {
5729  __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT_EXC(long, unsigned PY_LONG_LONG, PyLong_AsUnsignedLongLong(x))
5730 #endif
5731  }
5732  } else {
5733 #if CYTHON_USE_PYLONG_INTERNALS
5734  const digit* digits = ((PyLongObject*)x)->ob_digit;
5735  switch (Py_SIZE(x)) {
5736  case 0: return (long) 0;
5737  case -1: __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT(long, sdigit, (sdigit) (-(sdigit)digits[0]))
5738  case 1: __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT(long, digit, +digits[0])
5739  case -2:
5740  if (8 * sizeof(long) - 1 > 1 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
5741  if (8 * sizeof(unsigned long) > 2 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
5742  __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT(long, long, -(long) (((((unsigned long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[0])))
5743  } else if (8 * sizeof(long) - 1 > 2 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
5744  return (long) (((long)-1)*(((((long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (long)digits[0])));
5745  }
5746  }
5747  break;
5748  case 2:
5749  if (8 * sizeof(long) > 1 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
5750  if (8 * sizeof(unsigned long) > 2 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
5751  __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT(long, unsigned long, (((((unsigned long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[0])))
5752  } else if (8 * sizeof(long) - 1 > 2 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
5753  return (long) ((((((long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (long)digits[0])));
5754  }
5755  }
5756  break;
5757  case -3:
5758  if (8 * sizeof(long) - 1 > 2 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
5759  if (8 * sizeof(unsigned long) > 3 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
5760  __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT(long, long, -(long) (((((((unsigned long)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[0])))
5761  } else if (8 * sizeof(long) - 1 > 3 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
5762  return (long) (((long)-1)*(((((((long)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (long)digits[0])));
5763  }
5764  }
5765  break;
5766  case 3:
5767  if (8 * sizeof(long) > 2 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
5768  if (8 * sizeof(unsigned long) > 3 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
5769  __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT(long, unsigned long, (((((((unsigned long)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[0])))
5770  } else if (8 * sizeof(long) - 1 > 3 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
5771  return (long) ((((((((long)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (long)digits[0])));
5772  }
5773  }
5774  break;
5775  case -4:
5776  if (8 * sizeof(long) - 1 > 3 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
5777  if (8 * sizeof(unsigned long) > 4 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
5778  __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT(long, long, -(long) (((((((((unsigned long)digits[3]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[0])))
5779  } else if (8 * sizeof(long) - 1 > 4 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
5780  return (long) (((long)-1)*(((((((((long)digits[3]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (long)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (long)digits[0])));
5781  }
5782  }
5783  break;
5784  case 4:
5785  if (8 * sizeof(long) > 3 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
5786  if (8 * sizeof(unsigned long) > 4 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
5787  __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT(long, unsigned long, (((((((((unsigned long)digits[3]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[0])))
5788  } else if (8 * sizeof(long) - 1 > 4 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
5789  return (long) ((((((((((long)digits[3]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (long)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (long)digits[0])));
5790  }
5791  }
5792  break;
5793  }
5794 #endif
5795  if (sizeof(long) <= sizeof(long)) {
5796  __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT_EXC(long, long, PyLong_AsLong(x))
5797 #ifdef HAVE_LONG_LONG
5798  } else if (sizeof(long) <= sizeof(PY_LONG_LONG)) {
5799  __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT_EXC(long, PY_LONG_LONG, PyLong_AsLongLong(x))
5800 #endif
5801  }
5802  }
5803  {
5804 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_PYPY && !defined(_PyLong_AsByteArray)
5805  PyErr_SetString(PyExc_RuntimeError,
5806  "_PyLong_AsByteArray() not available in PyPy, cannot convert large numbers");
5807 #else
5808  long val;
5809  PyObject *v = __Pyx_PyNumber_IntOrLong(x);
5810  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
5811  if (likely(v) && !PyLong_Check(v)) {
5812  PyObject *tmp = v;
5813  v = PyNumber_Long(tmp);
5814  Py_DECREF(tmp);
5815  }
5816  #endif
5817  if (likely(v)) {
5818  int one = 1; int is_little = (int)*(unsigned char *)&one;
5819  unsigned char *bytes = (unsigned char *)&val;
5820  int ret = _PyLong_AsByteArray((PyLongObject *)v,
5821  bytes, sizeof(val),
5822  is_little, !is_unsigned);
5823  Py_DECREF(v);
5824  if (likely(!ret))
5825  return val;
5826  }
5827 #endif
5828  return (long) -1;
5829  }
5830  } else {
5831  long val;
5832  PyObject *tmp = __Pyx_PyNumber_IntOrLong(x);
5833  if (!tmp) return (long) -1;
5834  val = __Pyx_PyInt_As_long(tmp);
5835  Py_DECREF(tmp);
5836  return val;
5837  }
5838 raise_overflow:
5839  PyErr_SetString(PyExc_OverflowError,
5840  "value too large to convert to long");
5841  return (long) -1;
5842 raise_neg_overflow:
5843  PyErr_SetString(PyExc_OverflowError,
5844  "can't convert negative value to long");
5845  return (long) -1;
5846 }

5848 /* CIntFromPy */
5849 static CYTHON_INLINE int __Pyx_PyInt_As_int(PyObject *x) {
5850 #ifdef __Pyx_HAS_GCC_DIAGNOSTIC
5851 #pragma GCC diagnostic push
5852 #pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Wconversion"
5853 #endif
5854  const int neg_one = (int) -1, const_zero = (int) 0;
5855 #ifdef __Pyx_HAS_GCC_DIAGNOSTIC
5856 #pragma GCC diagnostic pop
5857 #endif
5858  const int is_unsigned = neg_one > const_zero;
5859 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
5860  if (likely(PyInt_Check(x))) {
5861  if (sizeof(int) < sizeof(long)) {
5862  __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT(int, long, PyInt_AS_LONG(x))
5863  } else {
5864  long val = PyInt_AS_LONG(x);
5865  if (is_unsigned && unlikely(val < 0)) {
5866  goto raise_neg_overflow;
5867  }
5868  return (int) val;
5869  }
5870  } else
5871 #endif
5872  if (likely(PyLong_Check(x))) {
5873  if (is_unsigned) {
5874 #if CYTHON_USE_PYLONG_INTERNALS
5875  const digit* digits = ((PyLongObject*)x)->ob_digit;
5876  switch (Py_SIZE(x)) {
5877  case 0: return (int) 0;
5878  case 1: __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT(int, digit, digits[0])
5879  case 2:
5880  if (8 * sizeof(int) > 1 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
5881  if (8 * sizeof(unsigned long) > 2 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
5882  __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT(int, unsigned long, (((((unsigned long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[0])))
5883  } else if (8 * sizeof(int) >= 2 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
5884  return (int) (((((int)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (int)digits[0]));
5885  }
5886  }
5887  break;
5888  case 3:
5889  if (8 * sizeof(int) > 2 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
5890  if (8 * sizeof(unsigned long) > 3 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
5891  __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT(int, unsigned long, (((((((unsigned long)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[0])))
5892  } else if (8 * sizeof(int) >= 3 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
5893  return (int) (((((((int)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (int)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (int)digits[0]));
5894  }
5895  }
5896  break;
5897  case 4:
5898  if (8 * sizeof(int) > 3 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
5899  if (8 * sizeof(unsigned long) > 4 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
5900  __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT(int, unsigned long, (((((((((unsigned long)digits[3]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[0])))
5901  } else if (8 * sizeof(int) >= 4 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
5902  return (int) (((((((((int)digits[3]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (int)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (int)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (int)digits[0]));
5903  }
5904  }
5905  break;
5906  }
5907 #endif
5908 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_CPYTHON && PY_VERSION_HEX < 0x030C00A7

6047  while (a) {

6054 static CYTHON_INLINE int __Pyx_IsSubtype(PyTypeObject *a, PyTypeObject *b) {
6055  PyObject *mro;
6056  if (a == b) return 1;
6057  mro = a->tp_mro;
6058  if (likely(mro)) {
6059  Py_ssize_t i, n;
6060  n = PyTuple_GET_SIZE(mro);
6061  for (i = 0; i < n; i++) {
6062  if (PyTuple_GET_ITEM(mro, i) == (PyObject *)b)
6063  return 1;
6064  }
6065  return 0;
6066  }
6067  return __Pyx_InBases(a, b);
6068 }

6070 static int __Pyx_inner_PyErr_GivenExceptionMatches2(PyObject *err, PyObject* exc_type1, PyObject* exc_type2) {
6071  PyObject *exception, *value, *tb;
6072  int res;
6073  __Pyx_PyThreadState_declare
6074  __Pyx_PyThreadState_assign

6084  PyErr_WriteUnraisable(err);
6085  res = 0;
6086  }
6087  }
6088  __Pyx_ErrRestore(exception, value, tb);
6089  return res;
6090 }

6094  if (!res) {

6100 static int __Pyx_PyErr_GivenExceptionMatchesTuple(PyObject *exc_type, PyObject *tuple) {
6101  Py_ssize_t i, n;
6102  assert(PyExceptionClass_Check(exc_type));
6103  n = PyTuple_GET_SIZE(tuple);
6104 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
6105  for (i=0; i<n; i++) {
6106  if (exc_type == PyTuple_GET_ITEM(tuple, i)) return 1;
6107  }
6108 #endif
6109  for (i=0; i<n; i++) {
6110  PyObject *t = PyTuple_GET_ITEM(tuple, i);
6111  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
6112  if (likely(exc_type == t)) return 1;
6113  #endif
6114  if (likely(PyExceptionClass_Check(t))) {
6115  if (__Pyx_inner_PyErr_GivenExceptionMatches2(exc_type, NULL, t)) return 1;
6116  } else {
6117  }
6118  }
6119  return 0;
6120 }
6121 static CYTHON_INLINE int __Pyx_PyErr_GivenExceptionMatches(PyObject *err, PyObject* exc_type) {
6122  if (likely(err == exc_type)) return 1;
6123  if (likely(PyExceptionClass_Check(err))) {
6124  if (likely(PyExceptionClass_Check(exc_type))) {
6125  return __Pyx_inner_PyErr_GivenExceptionMatches2(err, NULL, exc_type);
6126  } else if (likely(PyTuple_Check(exc_type))) {
6127  return __Pyx_PyErr_GivenExceptionMatchesTuple(err, exc_type);
6128  } else {
6129  }
6130  }
6131  return PyErr_GivenExceptionMatches(err, exc_type);
6132 }
6133 static CYTHON_INLINE int __Pyx_PyErr_GivenExceptionMatches2(PyObject *err, PyObject *exc_type1, PyObject *exc_type2) {
6134  assert(PyExceptionClass_Check(exc_type1));
6135  assert(PyExceptionClass_Check(exc_type2));
6136  if (likely(err == exc_type1 || err == exc_type2)) return 1;
6137  if (likely(PyExceptionClass_Check(err))) {
6138  return __Pyx_inner_PyErr_GivenExceptionMatches2(err, exc_type1, exc_type2);
6139  }
6140  return (PyErr_GivenExceptionMatches(err, exc_type1) || PyErr_GivenExceptionMatches(err, exc_type2));
6141 }

6144 /* CheckBinaryVersion */
6145 static int __Pyx_check_binary_version(void) {
6146  char ctversion[5];
6147  int same=1, i, found_dot;
6148  const char* rt_from_call = Py_GetVersion();
6149  PyOS_snprintf(ctversion, 5, "%d.%d", PY_MAJOR_VERSION, PY_MINOR_VERSION);
6150  found_dot = 0;
6151  for (i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
6152  if (!ctversion[i]) {
6153  same = (rt_from_call[i] < '0' || rt_from_call[i] > '9');
6154  break;
6155  }
6156  if (rt_from_call[i] != ctversion[i]) {
6157  same = 0;
6158  break;
6159  }
6160  }
6161  if (!same) {
6162  char rtversion[5] = {'\0'};
6163  char message[200];
6164  for (i=0; i<4; ++i) {
6165  if (rt_from_call[i] == '.') {
6166  if (found_dot) break;
6167  found_dot = 1;
6168  } else if (rt_from_call[i] < '0' || rt_from_call[i] > '9') {
6169  break;
6170  }
6171  rtversion[i] = rt_from_call[i];
6172  }
6173  PyOS_snprintf(message, sizeof(message),
6174  "compiletime version %s of module '%.100s' "
6175  "does not match runtime version %s",
6176  ctversion, __Pyx_MODULE_NAME, rtversion);
6177  return PyErr_WarnEx(NULL, message, 1);
6178  }
6179  return 0;
6180 }

6236 /* InitStrings */
6237 static int __Pyx_InitStrings(__Pyx_StringTabEntry *t) {
6238  while (t->p) {
6239  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
6240  if (t->is_unicode) {
6241  *t->p = PyUnicode_DecodeUTF8(t->s, t->n - 1, NULL);
6242  } else if (t->intern) {
6243  *t->p = PyString_InternFromString(t->s);
6244  } else {
6245  *t->p = PyString_FromStringAndSize(t->s, t->n - 1);
6246  }
6247  #else
6248  if (t->is_unicode | t->is_str) {
6249  if (t->intern) {
6250  *t->p = PyUnicode_InternFromString(t->s);
6251  } else if (t->encoding) {
6252  *t->p = PyUnicode_Decode(t->s, t->n - 1, t->encoding, NULL);
6253  } else {
6254  *t->p = PyUnicode_FromStringAndSize(t->s, t->n - 1);
6255  }
6256  } else {
6257  *t->p = PyBytes_FromStringAndSize(t->s, t->n - 1);
6258  }
6259  #endif
6260  if (!*t->p)
6261  return -1;
6262  if (PyObject_Hash(*t->p) == -1)
6263  return -1;
6264  ++t;
6265  }
6266  return 0;
6267 }

6373 static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject* __Pyx_PyNumber_IntOrLong(PyObject* x) {
6374 #if CYTHON_USE_TYPE_SLOTS
6375  PyNumberMethods *m;
6376 #endif
6377  const char *name = NULL;
6378  PyObject *res = NULL;
6379 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
6380  if (likely(PyInt_Check(x) || PyLong_Check(x)))
6381 #else
6382  if (likely(PyLong_Check(x)))
6383 #endif
6384  return __Pyx_NewRef(x);
6385 #if CYTHON_USE_TYPE_SLOTS
6386  m = Py_TYPE(x)->tp_as_number;
6387  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
6388  if (m && m->nb_int) {
6389  name = "int";
6390  res = m->nb_int(x);
6391  }
6392  else if (m && m->nb_long) {
6393  name = "long";
6394  res = m->nb_long(x);
6395  }
6396  #else
6397  if (likely(m && m->nb_int)) {
6398  name = "int";
6399  res = m->nb_int(x);
6400  }
6401  #endif
6402 #else
6403  if (!PyBytes_CheckExact(x) && !PyUnicode_CheckExact(x)) {
6404  res = PyNumber_Int(x);
6405  }
6406 #endif
6407  if (likely(res)) {
6408 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
6409  if (unlikely(!PyInt_Check(res) && !PyLong_Check(res))) {
6410 #else
6411  if (unlikely(!PyLong_CheckExact(res))) {
6412 #endif
6413  return __Pyx_PyNumber_IntOrLongWrongResultType(res, name);
6414  }
6415  }
6416  else if (!PyErr_Occurred()) {
6417  PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
6418  "an integer is required");
6419  }
